OL,3,CLabour vows to crack down on tax
OL,4,Cdodgers to fund NHS and schools pledges
OL,6,F"That process is now complete and the
OL,7,Ffunding a future Labour government
OL,8,Fwill raise from taking on the tax
OL,9,Fdodgers will fund more appointments in
OL,10,FNHS hospitals, new scanners, extra
OL,11,Fdentist appointments and free
OL,12,Fbreakfast clubs for all primary school
OL,13,Fpupils."
OL,15,FLabour said the tax gap had widened to
OL,16,F#36 billion in 2021/22 - #5 billion
OL,17,Fmore than it had been the previous
OL,18,Fyear, as an under-resourced HMRC
OL,19,Fstruggled to collect revenues and
OL,20,Fmanage compliance.
